remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` wraps a 32-bit unsigned integer that encodes four ASCII characters. These tags are used throughout OpenType and TrueType fonts to identify tables (`head`, `cmap`), variation axes (`wght`, `wdth`), and features (`kern`, `liga`).

You can construct a tag from four characters or from a raw `uint`, and implicit conversions make it interoperable with raw integer APIs.

## Examples

```csharp
// Construct from characters
var weightTag = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Parse from a string
var widthTag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth");

// Convert to string (round-trips the tag)
Console.WriteLine(weightTag.ToString()); // "wght"
```
